---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const PAGE_TITLE = 'EigenSelf — Understand yourself beyond labels';
const PAGE_DESCRIPTION =
	'EigenSelf helps you see the values quietly shaping your choices — and offers a hand-crafted Career Report for people navigating an important transition.';

const EMAIL = 'info@eigenself.ai';
const EXERCISE_URL = 'https://chenyux3.github.io/eigenself-survey/';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={PAGE_TITLE} description={PAGE_DESCRIPTION} />
		<style>
			.wordmark {
				width: 620px;
				max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2em 1em 0;
				font-weight: 600;
				font-size: 1em;
				color: var(--text-strong);
				letter-spacing: -0.01em;
			}
			.lede {
				font-size: 1.125em;
				color: var(--text);
				margin: 0 0 2em;
			}
			section {
				margin: 0 0 1em;
			}
			.cta-row {
				display: flex;
				align-items: center;
				gap: 1.25em;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
				margin: 1.75em 0 0;
			}
			.cta-primary {
				font-weight: 600;
			}
			.link-secondary {
				color: var(--text-muted);
				font-size: 0.95em;
				text-decoration: none;
			}
			.link-secondary:hover {
				color: var(--text);
			}
			.invitation {
				color: var(--text-muted);
				font-style: italic;
			}
			.diagram {
				text-align: center;
				line-height: 1.6;
			}
		</style>
	</head>
	<body>
		<div class="wordmark">EigenSelf</div>
		<main>
			<!-- 1. Hero -->
			<section>
				<h1>Understand yourself beyond labels.</h1>
				<p class="lede">
					You are more than your title, your type, and your résumé — but
					it's not always easy to say what that "more" is. EigenSelf helps
					you see the values quietly shaping your choices, and how they
					support, reinforce, and sometimes conflict with one another.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="cta-primary" href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}
						>Ask about a Career Report →</a
					>
					<a class="link-secondary" href={EXERCISE_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener"
						>Curious? Try the 3-minute Value Exercise →</a
					>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- 2. What is EigenSelf? -->
			<section>
				<h2>What is EigenSelf?</h2>
				<p>
					Not another personality test. Not career advice. A way to
					understand the values underlying your life and decisions — how
					they connect, reinforce, and pull against one another.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 3. The Career Report -->
			<section>
				<h2>The Career Report</h2>
				<p>
					A deeper, evidence-based reflection for people navigating an
					important career transition. Built from three inputs: the Value
					Exercise, your CV, and your own account of where you are.
				</p>
				<p class="invitation">
					Each report is analyzed by hand, so they're offered to a small
					number of people at a time.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-row">
					<a class="cta-primary" href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}
						>Ask about a Career Report</a
					>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- 4. How the Career Report Works -->
			<section>
				<h2>How the Career Report Works</h2>
				<pre class="diagram">{`Value Exercise
      +
CV and Internal Story
      ↓
Evidence and Pattern Analysis
      ↓
Value Network
      ↓
Personalized Career Report`}</pre>
				<p>
					Each report is grounded in the evidence of your own life — not
					generic personality categories.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 5. Why I Built EigenSelf -->
			<section>
				<h2>Why I Built EigenSelf</h2>
				<p>
					We live in an age that hands everyone a stack of labels — school,
					job, income, personality type, life stage. They make us legible to
					others, but they rarely explain how a person is actually put
					together inside. AI makes the question sharper: when skills and
					output can be replicated, what's left that is genuinely yours?
				</p>
				<p>
					I built EigenSelf to answer that — not with another label, but by
					looking at how your core values connect, reinforce, and pull
					against one another. That inner shape is the part no one can assign
					to you and no tool can replace.
				</p>
				<p>
					It began as something I needed myself, during my own transition. I
					didn't want a more optimized version of me — I wanted to see, more
					clearly and honestly, how I actually work, and move forward from
					there. EigenSelf is my attempt to make that kind of
					self-understanding available to ordinary people, not only those
					with the time, money, or right therapist to find it.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- 6. Closing -->
			<section>
				<h2>Where to Begin</h2>
				<p>
					For Career Report invitations or any other conversation, reach out
					at <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a>. Or start with the
					3-minute <a href={EXERCISE_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener"
						>Value Exercise</a
					> — a small glimpse into your value network.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
